flavorText: Strong, but not too bright, this Pokémon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging Tackles.
It squirts water forcefully from its mouth to shoot down flying prey.
This mysterious Pokémon started life as an ancient clay figurine made over 20,000 years ago.
It is described in mythology as the Pokémon that shaped the universe with its 1,000 arms.
With its long fangs, this surprisingly violent Pokémon can gnaw away even thick concrete with ease.
Burrows at high speed in search of food. The tunnels it leaves are used as homes by Diglett.
When exposed to the moon's aura, the rings on its body glow faintly and it gains a mysterious power.
It controls balls of fire. As it grows, its six tails split from their tips to make more tails.
It stores energy by sleeping at underwater depths at which no other life-forms can survive.
Made from soil, the shell on its back hardens when it drinks water. It lives along lakes.
When exposed to the moon's aura, the rings on its body glow faintly and it's filled with a mysterious power.
It gets picked on because it's meek. But then, whoever teased it gets to feel the full force of its horns and a good swatting from its thick tail.
On nights with a full moon, Clefairy gather from all over and dance. Bathing in moonlight makes them float.
Legends claim this Pokémon flies the world's skies continuously on its magnificent, seven-colored wings.
The males will do whatever the females tell them. They give the females most of their food. Due to malnutrition, the males can't evolve.
Strong, but not too bright, this Pokémon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging Tackles.
The trio is together from birth. It constantly gathers honey from flowers to please Vespiquen.
Its actual appearance is unknown. A scholar who saw what was under its rag was overwhelmed by horror and died of the shock.
It makes its nest at the bottom of swamps. It will eat anything—if it is alive, Whiscash will eat it.
Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a Poké Ball, it has zapped many people.
These Pokémon prefer a tidy habitat. They are always sweeping and dusting, using their tails as brooms.
It conveys its feelings using different cries. It works in a pack to cleverly take down prey.
A mythical Pokémon said to have swelled the seas with rain and tidal waves. It battled with Groudon.
It can make most any Pokémon run away simply by opening its mouth wide to reveal its big fangs.
Crackle…buzz…Dedenne…?! Beep…
One of the Ultra Beast life-forms, it was observed cutting down a gigantic steel tower with one stroke of its blade.
If its two tail feathers are standing at attention, it is proof of good health. It soars elegantly in the sky.
It makes its nest on steep sea cliffs. Riding updrafts, it soars to great heights.
Split into two, the tails are so adept at handling and doing things, Ambipom rarely uses its hands.
Possessing an unbalanced and unstable genetic makeup, it conceals many possible evolutions.
To protect itself from attackers, it curls up into a ball. It lives in arid regions with minimal rainfall.
It is told in mythology that this Pokémon was born before the universe even existed.
It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over if inhaled.
It generates ultrasonic waves by violently flapping its wings. After making its prey faint, it melts the prey with acid.
It is so timid, it can't move if it isn't with a swarm of others. It conveys its feelings with scent.
Its hardy vitality enables it to adapt to any environment. Its pincers will never release prey.
With power equal to an excavator, it can dig through dense bedrock. It's a huge help during tunnel construction.
Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.
At the time of birth, it has just one tail. Its tail splits from the tip as it grows older.
If anyone dares to grab its hilt, it wraps a blue cloth around that person's arm and drains that person's life energy completely.
It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.
It stores berries in its shell. The berries eventually ferment to become delicious juices.
Displaying amazing teamwork, they follow the orders of their boss as they all help out in the search for their favorite berries.
It is nocturnal in nature. If it spots something shiny, its eyes glitter brightly.
This is an extremely rare Meowth card. Maybe good fortune will come to you if you hold this card!
When she's surrounded by cushions and dressers that I like, she looks just like a princess!
Salazzle lives deep in caves and forces the Salandit it has attracted with its pheromones to serve it.
It is said to have emerged from an egg in a place where there was nothing, then shaped the world.
Loads weighing up to 50 times as much as its own body weight pose no issue for this Pokémon. It's skilled at making use of mud.

name_en: Head Ringer Team Flare Hyper Gear

flavorText: It spends nearly all its time in a day sprawled out. Just seeing it makes one drowsy.
It lived on the seafloor 100 million years ago and was reanimated scientifically.
A Pokémon that lives on icebergs. It swims in the sea using the point on its head to break up ice.
Often targeted by bird Pokémon, it desperately resists by releasing poison from its tail spikes.
Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.
The eggs laid by Chansey are rich in nutrients and a favorite food of many Pokémon.
Their white fur is coated in a special oil that makes it easy for them to deflect attacks.
Their ears are sensitive enough to hear a pin drop from over a mile away, so they're usually found in quiet places.
A clay slab with cursed engravings took possession of a Yamask. The slab is said to be absorbing the Yamask's dark power.
It can't stop itself from chasing moving things, and it runs in a circle, chasing its own tail.
This is Zygarde's form at times when it uses its overwhelming power to suppress those who endanger the ecosystem.
It is highly attuned to the emotions of people and Pokémon. It hides if it senses hostility.
It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.
Known as "The Desert Spirit," this Pokémon hides in the sandstorms it causes by beating its wings.
Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokémon conceals many different possible evolutions.
When it's happy, Glameow demonstrates beautiful movements of its tail, like a dancing ribbon.
Its steps are staggering and unsteady, but Spinda thinks it's walking in a straight line.
It walks in zigzag fashion. It is good at finding items in the grass and even in the ground.
It loves to eat leaves. If it is attacked by a STARLY, it will defend itself with its spiked rear.
It moves less than an inch a year, but when it's in a jam, it will spin and drill down into the ground in a split second.
It rarely fights fairly, but that is strictly to ensure survival. It is popular as a mascot.
A Pokémon with abundant curiosity. It shows an interest in everything, so it always zigzags.
Even the most ferocious Pokémon become calm when they eat Blissey's egg, which is said to be filled with happiness.
A powerful curse was woven into an ancient painting. After absorbing the spirit of a Yamask, the painting began to move.
It races through narrow caves, using its sharp claws to catch prey. The skin on its face is harder than a rock.
Its heart beats at a tenfold tempo, so it cannot sit still for even a moment.
Its tongue is twice the length of its body. It can be moved like an arm for grabbing food and attacking.
When it finds a flower it likes, it dwells on that flower its whole life long. It floats in the wind's embrace with an untroubled heart.
When Mom gets in the kitchen, the happiest things happen. I can feel my mouth watering!
It can't live without the stalk it holds. That's why it defends the stalk from attackers with its life.
Often found in forests, eating leaves. It has a sharp, venomous stinger on its head.
Its jaws are strong enough to crush rocks but so heavy that it can't get up if it flips over. Sandile seize those moments as their chance.
The brains in its two heads appear to communicate emotions to each other with telepathic power.
It charges prey at speeds over 60 mph. However, because it can only run straight, it often fails.
It is told in mythology that this Pokémon was born before the universe even existed.
When the flowers of a well-tended flower bed bloom, it appears and celebrates with an elegant dance.
It can reconstitute its entire cellular structure to change into what it sees, but it returns to normal when it relaxes.
Their saliva contains lots of components that can dissolve anything. The numbness caused by their lick does not dissipate.
To make itself appear intimidatingly beefy, it tightly cinches its waist with its twin tails.
Grave robbers who mistake them for real coffins and get too close end up trapped inside their bodies.
With its steel-hard stone head, it headbutts indiscriminately. This is because of the stress it feels at being unable to fly.

name_en: Jamming Net Team Flare Hyper Gear

flavorText: From holes in its palms, it fires out Geodude. Its carapace can withstand volcanic eruptions.
After two Binacle find a suitably sized rock, they adhere themselves to it and live together. They cooperate to gather food during high tide.
Because it doesn't yelp, it's extremely popular with Trainers who live in apartment buildings.
It loves vengeful emotions and hangs in rows under the eaves of houses where vengeful people live.
It is described in mythology as the Pokémon that shaped the universe with its 1,000 arms.
The complex attack patterns of its two swords are unstoppable, even for an opponent greatly accomplished at swordplay.
Even though its helpless, gaseous body can be blown away by the slightest breeze, it doesn't seem to care.
Its total control over the boundaries of space enable it to transport itself to faraway places or even other dimensions.
It's very curious, but its means of investigating things is to try to punch them with its tentacles. The search for food is what brings it onto land.
Mud that hardens around a Mudsdale's legs sets harder than stone. It's so hard that it allows this Pokémon to scrap a truck with a single kick.
The world's laziest Pokémon. When it is lounging, it is actually saving energy for striking back.
The twinkle of the stars. The destiny of love. A miracle that grants wishes in the night sky.
Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.
It dislikes dirty places. It often searches for a comfortable place in which to groom itself.
It has a gutsy spirit that makes it bravely take on tough foes. It flies in search of warm climates.
Only Farfetch'd that have survived many battles can attain this evolution. When this Pokémon's leek withers, it will retire from combat.
It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.
The brains in its two heads appear to communicate emotions to each other with a telepathic power.
